Vice president, Professor Yemi Osinbanjo is in Bauchi to condole the families, Bauchi State governmentâ€Ž and people of the state over the death of late Senator Ali Wakili. The vice president arrived Bauchi Sunday through the Abubakar Tafawa Balewa International Airport. He is expected to visit and condole the late senator's residence located on Kano road GRA Bauchi, the Bauchi State government house to meet with governor Mohammed Abdullahi Abubakar and later the emir of Bauchi, Dr Rilwanu Suleiman Adamu to condole him and the emirate. Senator Ali Wakili died early morning on Saturday, March 17th, 2018 after a brief illness. Details later.